From e666675c76ec1b6c9cbd1f2673beee7644dbfcae Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrei Aldea <andrei1998@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 18:55:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 02/20] rpmsg: char: update dynamic endpoint source address

TI's ti-rpmsg-char userspace library opens a newly-created rpmsg
endpoint and then reads the endpoint's sysfs src attribute to discover
the kernel-allocated local endpoint address.

When the endpoint was requested with RPMSG_ADDR_ANY, mainline rpmsg-char
left chinfo.src as RPMSG_ADDR_ANY even after rpmsg_create_ept() allocated
a concrete local address. That causes older TI userspace to reject the
endpoint with "get_local_endpt failed -1".

Mirror TI's downstream behavior by recording the allocated endpoint
address in chinfo.src once the endpoint has been opened.

Assisted-by: Codex <codex@openai.com>
---
 drivers/rpmsg/rpmsg_char.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/rpmsg/rpmsg_char.c b/drivers/rpmsg/rpmsg_char.c
index bff5aefe..788da7b3 100644
--- a/drivers/rpmsg/rpmsg_char.c
+++ b/drivers/rpmsg/rpmsg_char.c
@@ -176,6 +176,9 @@ static int rpmsg_eptdev_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *filp)
 
 	ept->flow_cb = rpmsg_ept_flow_cb;
 	eptdev->ept = ept;
+	if (eptdev->chinfo.src == RPMSG_ADDR_ANY)
+		eptdev->chinfo.src = ept->addr;
+
 	filp->private_data = eptdev;
 	mutex_unlock(&eptdev->ept_lock);
 
